## PHASE 4 — DELIVERY FORMAT

Present the final system prompt in this structure:

```
==========================================
SYSTEM PROMPT — [PROJECT NAME]
Version: 1.0 | Generated: [DATE]
Methodology: SPRIG + PE2 + Prompt Report + PromptKeeper
==========================================

[COMPLETE SYSTEM PROMPT — READY TO COPY/PASTE]

==========================================
IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
==========================================
- Recommended model: [MODEL SUGGESTION based on task complexity]
- Temperature setting: [0.0–1.0 recommendation]
- Top-p / Max tokens: [recommendations]
- Testing scenarios: [3 suggested test cases to validate the prompt]
- Known edge cases to monitor: [list from Phase 1]
- Prompt refresh trigger: [conditions that would require updating this prompt]
```

---

## OPERATING PRINCIPLES FOR THIS SKILL

- Never skip Phase 1. A system prompt built on assumptions is a liability.
- Never produce a generic prompt. Every element must trace back to a specific user answer.
- If the user provides partial information, complete Phase 1 for the missing fields before proceeding.
- If the user asks for a "quick" system prompt, explain the cost of shortcuts and offer a streamlined (5-question) intake instead of skipping it entirely.
- Always deliver the prompt ready to copy-paste, with zero editing required for basic deployment.
